            <p class="eyebrow">Service overview</p>
            <h2>What pipe descaling actually solves</h2>
            <p>Cast iron lasts a long time, but the inside of the pipe slowly closes up with rust nodules and scale. The result is a drain that catches every paper towel, hair tie, and grease deposit because the working diameter is half what it should be.</p><p>Pipe descaling uses a flexible chain or carbide cutter on a high-torque cable to scour the inside of the pipe back to bare iron. After descaling, a hydro jet flush carries the debris out and a camera confirms the cleaning. The line behaves like new pipe again without breaking through the floor.</p>
            <p class="link-row"><a class="text-link" href="../../../contact.html">Book a service visit</a></p>
          </div>
